timetraMsdpMIBModule.name: timetraMsdpMIBModule

revisions.description: Rev 10.0 1 Aug 2011 00:00 10.0 release of the TIMETRA-MSDP-MIB.
Rev 7.0 28 Feb 2009 00:00 7.0 release of the TIMETRA-MSDP-MIB.
Rev 0.1 1 Aug 2006 00:00 Initial version of the TIMETRA-MSDP-MIB.

timetraMsdpMIBModule.description: This is the SNMP MIB module to manage and provision MSDP protocol on Alcatel SROS equipment. The Multicast Source Discovery Protocol (MSDP) is used to connect multicast routing domains. It typically runs on the same router as the Protocol Independent Multicast (PIM) sparse-mode rendezvous point (RP). Each MSDP router establishes adjacencies with internal and external MSDP peers similar to the Border Gateway Protocol (BGP). These peer routers inform each other about active sources within the domain. When they detect active sources, the routers can send PIM sparse-mode explicit join messages to the active source. tmnxMsdpMaxActiveSources.name: tmnxMsdpMaxActiveSources
tmnxMsdpMaxActiveSources.description: The value of tmnxMsdpMaxActiveSources specifies the maximum number of source active messages that will be accepted by MSDP. This effectively controls the number of source active messages that can be stored on the system. By default, no limit is placed on the number of source active messages and this is specified by the value '-1'. A value of 0 means that no source active messages will be accepted.

tmnxMsdpMsgRcvRate.name: tmnxMsdpMsgRcvRate
tmnxMsdpMsgRcvRate.description: The value of tmnxMsdpMsgRcvRate specifies the number of MSDP messages (including source active messages) that are read from the TCP session per tmnxMsdpMsgRcvRateTime seconds. By default, no MSDP messages are read from the TCP session and this is specified by the value 0. Once the number of MSDP packets defined in tmnxMsdpMsgRcvRateThd have been processed the rate of all other MSDP packets is rate limited by no longer accepting messages from the TCP session until tmnxMsdpMsgRcvRateTime seconds have elapsed.

tmnxMsdpMsgRcvRateTime.name: tmnxMsdpMsgRcvRateTime
tmnxMsdpMsgRcvRateTime.description: The value of tmnxMsdpMsgRcvRateTime specifies the time in seconds that together with tmnxMsdpMsgRcvRate defines the number of MSDP messages (including source active messages) that are read from the TCP session within the configured number of seconds. By default, no MSDP messages are read from the TCP session and this is specified by the value 0. Once the number of MSDP packets defined in tmnxMsdpMsgRcvRateThd have been processed the rate of all other MSDP packets is rate limited by no longer accepting messages from the TCP session until tmnxMsdpMsgRcvRateTime seconds have elapsed.

tmnxMsdpMsgRcvRateThd.name: tmnxMsdpMsgRcvRateThd
tmnxMsdpMsgRcvRateThd.description: The value of tmnxMsdpMsgRcvRateThd specifies the number of MSDP messages that can be processed before tmnxMsdpMsgRcvRate is set. This is useful during system startup and initialization. By default, no MSDP messages are read from the TCP session and this is specified by the value 0. Once the number of MSDP packets defined in tmnxMsdpMsgRcvRateThd have been processed the rate of all other MSDP packets is rate limited by no longer accepting messages from the TCP session until tmnxMsdpMsgRcvRateTime seconds have elapsed.

tmnxMsdpDataEncapsulation.name: tmnxMsdpDataEncapsulation
tmnxMsdpDataEncapsulation.description: The value of tmnxMsdpDataEncapsulation is used to configure a rendezvous point (RP) using MSDP to encapsulate multicast data received in MSDP register messages inside forwarded MSDP source-active messages. By default data encapsulation is enabled.

tmnxMsdpAdminState.name: tmnxMsdpAdminState
tmnxMsdpAdminState.description: The value of tmnxMsdpAdminState specifies the desired administrative state for MSDP. When MSDP is 'outOfService' the operational state of MSDP as well as the operational state of other entities under it, like peer or peer group is also disabled. By default, state of MSDP is 'inService'.

tmnxMsdpExportPolicy1.name: tmnxMsdpExportPolicy1
tmnxMsdpExportPolicy1.description: The value of tmnxMsdpExportPolicy1 specifies the export policy to export Source Active (SA) state from the SA list into MSDP. A maximum of five policy names can be specified. tmnxMsdpExportPolicy1 specifies policy number 1 at the protocol level. By default no export policies are applied and all SA entries are announced.

tmnxMsdpLocalAddressType.name: tmnxMsdpLocalAddressType
tmnxMsdpLocalAddressType.description: The value of tmnxMsdpLocalAddressType indicates the type of tmnxMsdpLocalAddress.

tmnxMsdpLocalAddress.name: tmnxMsdpLocalAddress
tmnxMsdpLocalAddress.description: The value of tmnxMsdpLocalAddress is used to configure the local end of a MSDP session. In order for MSDP to function at least one peer must be configured. When configuring a peer, the local end of the MSDP session must be configured. This address is used to validate incoming connections to the peer and to establish connections to the remote peer. By default no local address is configured.

tmnxMsdpStatusPeerCount.name: tmnxMsdpStatusPeerCount
tmnxMsdpStatusPeerCount.description: The value of tmnxMsdpStatusPeerCount indicates the number of configured peers.

tmnxMsdpStatusPeersEstablished.name: tmnxMsdpStatusPeersEstablished
tmnxMsdpStatusPeersEstablished.description: The value of tmnxMsdpStatusPeersEstablished indicates the number of peers in established state

tmnxMsdpStatusSACount.name: tmnxMsdpStatusSACount
tmnxMsdpStatusSACount.description: The value of tmnxMsdpStatusSACount indicates the number of source active configured in cache.

tmnxMsdpStatusLastTimeUp.name: tmnxMsdpStatusLastTimeUp
tmnxMsdpStatusLastTimeUp.description: The value of tmnxMsdpStatusLastTimeUp indicates the last time the protocol was enabled.

tmnxMsdpStatusActSrcLimExceeded.name: tmnxMsdpStatusActSrcLimExceeded
tmnxMsdpStatusActSrcLimExceeded.description: The value of tmnxMsdpStatusActSrcLimExceeded indicates the number of times the global active source limit has been exceeded

tmnxMsdpRpfLookupSequence.name: tmnxMsdpRpfLookupSequence
tmnxMsdpRpfLookupSequence.description: tmnxMsdpRpfLookupSequence is used to configure the sequence of route tables that MSDP uses for finding a Reverse Path Forwarding(RPF) interface for a particular multicast route. 'mucastRouteTable' is the unicast route table to be used only by multicast protocols(MSDP) which will contain routes submitted by multi-protocol BGP, ISIS and OSPF. 'ucastRouteTable' is the regular unicast route table which will contain routes submitted by all the unicast routing protocols. By default, only the 'ucastRouteTable' is looked up by MSDP for calculating RPF interface towards the source/rendezvous point. However the operator can specify the following: a) Use unicast route table only b) Use multicast unicast route table only or c) Use both the route tables. In case of (c), MSDP will always lookup first in the 'mucastRouteTable' and if there is a route, it will use it. If MSDP does not find a route in the first lookup, it will try to find it in the 'ucastRouteTable'.

tmnxMsdpSACacheLifetime.name: tmnxMsdpSACacheLifetime
tmnxMsdpSACacheLifetime.description: The value of tmnxMsdpSACacheLifetime specifies lifetime given to SA cache entries in seconds when created or refreshed. This object does not measure time per se; instead, it is the delta from the time at which an SA message is received at which it should be expired if not refreshed. (i.e., it is the value of tmnxMsdpSrcActiveExpiryTime immediately after receiving an SA message applying to that row.)

tmnxMsdpSARejectExportPolicy.name: tmnxMsdpSARejectExportPolicy
tmnxMsdpSARejectExportPolicy.description: The value of tmnxMsdpSARejectExportPolicy indicates number of SA messages that were not sent due to export policy.

tmnxMsdpSARejectImportPolicy.name: tmnxMsdpSARejectImportPolicy
tmnxMsdpSARejectImportPolicy.description: The value of tmnxMsdpSARejectImportPolicy indicates number of SA messages that were rejected due to import policy.

tmnxMsdpPeerTable.name: tmnxMsdpPeerTable
tmnxMsdpPeerTable.description: The tmnxMsdpPeerTable table provides information on the properties of a MSDP peer.

tmnxMsdpPeerEntry.name: tmnxMsdpPeerEntry
tmnxMsdpPeerEntry.description: tmnxMsdpPeerEntry represents a row entry in tmnxMsdpPeerTable for a MSDP peer. Entries can be created and deleted via SNMP SET operations through tmnxMsdpPeerRowStatus.

tmnxMsdpPeerAddressType.name: tmnxMsdpPeerAddressType
tmnxMsdpPeerAddressType.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerAddressType indicates the type of tmnxMsdpPeerAddress.

tmnxMsdpPeerAddress.name: tmnxMsdpPeerAddress
tmnxMsdpPeerAddress.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerAddress indicates the address of the MSDP peer.

tmnxMsdpPeerRowStatus.name: tmnxMsdpPeerRowStatus
tmnxMsdpPeerRowStatus.description: tmnxMsdpPeerRowStatus is the object used for creating and deleting row entries in this table.

tmnxMsdpPeerAuthKey.name: tmnxMsdpPeerAuthKey
tmnxMsdpPeerAuthKey.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerAuthKey specifies the authentication key to be used for a specific MSDP peering session. Authentication is done using the MD-5 message based digest protocol. Authentication cannot be configured globally and can be applied per peer only. The authentication key can be any combination of letters or numbers. Note that the string may contain embedded nulls. By default, all MSDP messages are accepted and the MD5 signature option authentication key is disabled

tmnxMsdpPeerAuthKeyEncrypted.name: tmnxMsdpPeerAuthKeyEncrypted
tmnxMsdpPeerAuthKeyEncrypted.description: When the value of tmnxMsdpPeerAuthKeyEncrypted is 'true', the password specified by tmnxMsdpPeerAuthKey is in the encrypted form. When the value of tmnxMsdpPeerAuthKeyEncrypted is 'false', the password specified by tmnxMsdpPeerAuthKey is in plain text. tmnxMsdpPeerAuthKey and tmnxMsdpPeerAuthKeyEncrypted, which indicates whether or not the password string is encrypted, must be set together in the same SNMP request PDU or else the set request will fail with an inconsistentValue error.

tmnxMsdpPeerDefaultPeer.name: tmnxMsdpPeerDefaultPeer
tmnxMsdpPeerDefaultPeer.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerDefaultPeer is used to configure a peer as the default Msdp peer due to which all source-active messages from the peer will be accepted without the usual peer-reverse-path-forwarding (RPF) check.

tmnxMsdpPeerAdminState.name: tmnxMsdpPeerAdminState
tmnxMsdpPeerAdminState.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerAdminState specifies the desired administrative state for a MSDP peer. When a MSDP peer is 'outOfService' the operational state of MSDP as well as the operational state of other entities under it, like peer group is also disabled. By default, the state of a MSDP peer is 'inService'.

tmnxMsdpPeerState.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerState indicates the status of the connection.

tmnxMsdpPeerLastUpOrDown.name: tmnxMsdpPeerLastUpOrDown
tmnxMsdpPeerLastUpOrDown.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerLastUpOrDown indicates the time at which the most recent peer-state change occurred.

tmnxMsdpPeerConRetry.name: tmnxMsdpPeerConRetry
tmnxMsdpPeerConRetry.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerConRetry indicates number of peer connection retry attempts.

tmnxMsdpPeerStateTimer.name: tmnxMsdpPeerStateTimer
tmnxMsdpPeerStateTimer.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerStateTimer indicates the number of seconds to wait before another message is sent to a peer.

tmnxMsdpPeerTimeout.name: tmnxMsdpPeerTimeout
tmnxMsdpPeerTimeout.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerTimeout indicates the number of seconds to wait for a response from the peer before declaring the peer unavailable.

tmnxMsdpPeerSAAccepted.name: tmnxMsdpPeerSAAccepted
tmnxMsdpPeerSAAccepted.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerSAAccepted indicates the number of entries in the source-active cache accepted from the peer.

tmnxMsdpPeerSARecvd.name: tmnxMsdpPeerSARecvd
tmnxMsdpPeerSARecvd.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerSARecvd indicates the number of entries in the source-active cache received by the peer.

tmnxMsdpPeerLastASLimit.name: tmnxMsdpPeerLastASLimit
tmnxMsdpPeerLastASLimit.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerLastASLimit indicates the time that the last active source limit was triggered.

tmnxMsdpPeerGroupTable.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGroupTable
tmnxMsdpPeerGroupTable.description: The tmnxMsdpPeerGroupTable provides a listing of all MSDP Peer Groups.

tmnxMsdpPeerGroupEntry.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGroupEntry
tmnxMsdpPeerGroupEntry.description: tmnxMsdpPeerGroupEntry represents a MSDP Peer Group. Entries can be created and deleted via SNMP SET operations.

tmnxMsdpPeerGroupName.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGroupName
tmnxMsdpPeerGroupName.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerGroupName indicates the peer group name.

tmnxMsdpPeerGroupRowStatus.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGroupRowStatus

tmnxMsdpPeerGroupImportPolicy1.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerGroupImportPolicy1 specifies the import policy number 1 at peer group level.

tmnxMsdpPeerGroupImportPolicy2.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGroupImportPolicy2
tmnxMsdpPeerGroupImportPolicy2.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerGroupImportPolicy2 specifies the import policy number 2 at peer group level.

tmnxMsdpPeerGroupImportPolicy3.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGroupImportPolicy3
tmnxMsdpPeerGroupImportPolicy3.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerGroupImportPolicy3 specifies the import policy number 3 at peer group level.

tmnxMsdpPeerGroupImportPolicy4.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGroupImportPolicy4
tmnxMsdpPeerGroupImportPolicy4.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerGroupImportPolicy4 specifies the import policy number 4 at peer group level.

tmnxMsdpPeerGroupImportPolicy5.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGroupImportPolicy5
tmnxMsdpPeerGroupImportPolicy5.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerGroupImportPolicy5 specifies the import policy number 5 at peer group level.

tmnxMsdpPeerGroupLocalAddrType.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGroupLocalAddrType
tmnxMsdpPeerGroupLocalAddrType.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerGroupLocalAddrType is used to configure the type of tmnxMsdpPeerGroupLocalAddress.

tmnxMsdpPeerGroupLocalAddress.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGroupLocalAddress
tmnxMsdpPeerGroupLocalAddress.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerGroupLocalAddress is used to configure the local end of a MSDP session. In order for MSDP to function at least one peer must be configured. When configuring a peer, the local end of the MSDP session must be configured. This address is used to validate incoming connections to the peer and to establish connections to the remote peer. By default no local address is configured.

tmnxMsdpPeerGroupMode.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGroupMode
tmnxMsdpPeerGroupMode.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerGroupMode is used to configure groups of peers in a full mesh topology. MSDP peers can be grouped in a full-mesh topology that prevents excessive flooding of source-active messages to neighboring peers. When operating in meshed mode, source-active messages received from a mesh group member are always accepted but are not flooded to other members of the same mesh group. As a result, these source-active messages are only flooded to non-mesh group peers or members of other mesh groups. By default 'standard' (non-meshed) mode is used.

tmnxMsdpPeerGroupMaxActSources.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGroupMaxActSources
tmnxMsdpPeerGroupMaxActSources.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerGroupMaxActSources specifies the maximum number of source active messages that will be accepted by this MSDP peer group. This effectively controls the number of active sources that can be stored on the system. By default, no limit is placed on the number of source active messages and this is specified by the value '-1'. A value of 0 means that no source active messages will be accepted.

tmnxMsdpPeerGroupActMsgsExMax.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGroupActMsgsExMax
tmnxMsdpPeerGroupActMsgsExMax.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerGroupActMsgsExMax indicates the number of source active messages received from this group that exceeded the established maximum number.

tmnxMsdpPeerGrpSARejExpPolicy.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGrpSARejExpPolicy
tmnxMsdpPeerGrpSARejExpPolicy.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerGrpSARejExpPolicy indicates the number of source active messages received from this group that were were not sent due to export policy.

tmnxMsdpPeerGrpSARejImpPolicy.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGrpSARejImpPolicy
tmnxMsdpPeerGrpSARejImpPolicy.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerGrpSARejImpPolicy indicates the number of source active messages received from this group that were rejected due to import policy.

tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerTable.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerTable
tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerTable.description: The tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerTable table provides a listing of all peers under MSDP Peer Groups.

tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerEntry.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerEntry
tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerEntry.description: An entry representing a peer in an MSDP Peer Group. Entries can be created and deleted via SNMP SET operations.

tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerAddressType.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerAddressType
tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerAddressType.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerAddressType indicates the type of address of the MSDP peer.

tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerAddress.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerAddress
tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerAddress.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerAddress indicates the address of the MSDP peer.

tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerRowStatus.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerRowStatus
tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerRowStatus.description: tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerRowStatus is the object used for creating and deleting row entries in this table.

tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerMaxActSrcs.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerMaxActSrcs
tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerMaxActSrcs.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerMaxActSrcs specifies the maximum number of source active messages that will be accepted by MSDP peer group peer. This effectively controls the number of active sources that can be stored on the system. By default, no limit is placed on the number of source active messages and this is specified by the value '-1'. A value of 0 means that no source active messages will be accepted.

tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerMsgRcvRt.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerMsgRcvRt
tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerMsgRcvRt.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerMsgRcvRt specifies the number of MSDP messages (including source active messages) that are read from the TCP session per tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerMsgRcvRtTime seconds. By default, no MSDP messages are read from the TCP session and this is specified by the value 0. Once the number of MSDP packets defined in tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerMsgRcvRtThd have been processed the rate of all other MSDP packets is rate limited by no longer accepting messages from the TCP session until tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerMsgRcvRtTime seconds have elapsed.

tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerMsgRcvRtTime.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerMsgRcvRtTime
tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerMsgRcvRtTime.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerMsgRcvRtTime specifies the time in seconds that together with tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerMsgRcvRt defines the number of MSDP messages (including source active messages) that are read from the TCP session within the configured number of seconds. By default, no MSDP messages are read from the TCP session and this is specified by the value 0. Once the number of MSDP packets defined in tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerMsgRcvRtThd have been processed the rate of all other MSDP packets is rate limited by no longer accepting messages from the TCP session until tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerMsgRcvRtTime seconds have elapsed.

tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerMsgRcvRtThd.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerMsgRcvRtThd
tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerMsgRcvRtThd.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerMsgRcvRtThd specifies the number of MSDP messages that can be processed before tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerMsgRcvRt is set. This is useful during system startup and initialization. By default, no MSDP messages are read from the TCP session and this is specified by the value 0. Once the number of MSDP packets defined in tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerMsgRcvRtThd have been processed the rate of all other MSDP packets is rate limited by no longer accepting messages from the TCP session until tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerMsgRcvRtTime seconds have elapsed.

tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerAuthKey.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerAuthKey
tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerAuthKey.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerAuthKey specifies the authentication key to be used for a specific MSDP peer group peering session. Authentication is done using the MD-5 message based digest protocol. Authentication cannot be configured globally and can be applied per peer only. The authentication key can be any combination of letters or numbers. Note that the string may contain embedded nulls. By default all MSDP messages are accepted and the MD5 signature option authentication key is disabled

tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerAKeyEncrypt.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerAKeyEncrypt
tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerAKeyEncrypt.description: When the value of tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerAKeyEncrypt is 'true', the password specified by tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerAuthKey is in the encrypted form. When the value of tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerAKeyEncrypt is 'false', the password specified by tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerAuthKey is in plain text. tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerAuthKey and tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerAKeyEncrypt, which indicates whether or not the password string is encrypted, must be set together in the same SNMP request PDU or else the set request will fail with an inconsistentValue error.

tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerDefaultPeer.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerDefaultPeer
tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerDefaultPeer.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerDefaultPeer is used to configure a peer as the default MSDP peer due to which all source-active messages from the peer will be accepted without the usual peer-reverse-path-forwarding (RPF) check.

tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerAdminState.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerAdminState
tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerAdminState.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerAdminState specifies the desired administrative state for a peer under a MSDP peer group. When tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerAdminState is 'outOfService' the operational state of the MSDP peer is disabled. By default, tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerAdminState is 'inService'.

tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerExportPolicy1.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerExportPolicy1
tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerExportPolicy1.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerExportPolicy1 specifies the export policy to export Source Active (SA) state from the SA list into MSDP. A maximum of five policy names can be specified. tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerExportPolicy1 specifies policy number 1 at the protocol level. By default no export policies are applied and all SA entries are announced.

tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerExportPolicy2.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerExportPolicy2
tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerExportPolicy2.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerExportPolicy2 specifies the export policy to export Source Active (SA) state from the SA list into MSDP. tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerExportPolicy2 specifies policy number 2 at the protocol level. By default no export policies are applied and all SA entries are announced.

tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerExportPolicy3.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerExportPolicy3
tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerExportPolicy3.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerExportPolicy3 specifies the export policy to export Source Active (SA) state from the SA list into MSDP. tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerExportPolicy3 specifies policy number 3 at the protocol level. By default no export policies are applied and all SA entries are announced.

tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerExportPolicy4.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerExportPolicy4
tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerExportPolicy4.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerExportPolicy4 specifies the export policy to export Source Active (SA) state from the SA list into MSDP. tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerExportPolicy4 specifies policy number 4 at the protocol level. By default no export policies are applied and all SA entries are announced.

tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerExportPolicy5.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerExportPolicy5
tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerExportPolicy5.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerExportPolicy5 specifies the export policy to export Source Active (SA) state from the SA list into MSDP. tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerExportPolicy1 specifies policy number 5 at the protocol level. By default no export policies are applied and all SA entries are announced.

tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerImportPolicy1.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerImportPolicy1
tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerImportPolicy1.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerImportPolicy1 specifies the import policy to import Source Active (SA) state from the SA list into MSDP. A maximum of five policy names can be specified. tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerImportPolicy1 specifies policy number 1 at the protocol level. By default no import policies are applied and all SA entries are announced.

tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerImportPolicy2.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerImportPolicy2
tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerImportPolicy2.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerImportPolicy2 specifies the import policy to import Source Active (SA) state from the SA list into MSDP. tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerImportPolicy2 specifies policy number 2 at the protocol level. By default no import policies are applied and all SA entries are announced.

tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerImportPolicy3.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerImportPolicy3
tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerImportPolicy3.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerImportPolicy3 specifies the import policy to import Source Active (SA) state from the SA list into MSDP. tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerImportPolicy3 specifies policy number 3 at the protocol level. By default no import policies are applied and all SA entries are announced.

tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerImportPolicy4.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerImportPolicy4
tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerImportPolicy4.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerImportPolicy4 specifies the import policy to import Source Active (SA) state from the SA list into MSDP. tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerImportPolicy4 specifies policy number 4 at the protocol level. By default no import policies are applied and all SA entries are announced.

tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerImportPolicy5.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerImportPolicy5
tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerImportPolicy5.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerImportPolicy5 specifies the import policy to import Source Active (SA) state from the SA list into MSDP. tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerImportPolicy5 specifies policy number 5 at the protocol level. By default no import policies are applied and all SA entries are announced.

tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerLocAddrType.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerLocAddrType
tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerLocAddrType.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerLocAddrType indicates the type of tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerLocalAddress.

tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerLocalAddress.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerLocalAddress
tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerLocalAddress.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerLocalAddress is used to configure the local end of a MSDP session. In order for MSDP to function at least one peer must be configured. When configuring a peer, the local end of the MSDP session must be configured. This address is used to validate incoming connections to the peer and to establish connections to the remote peer. By default no local address is configured.

tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerState.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerState
tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerState.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerState indicates the status of the connection.

tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerLastUpOrDown.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerLastUpOrDown
tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerLastUpOrDown.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerLastUpOrDown indicates the time at which the most recent peer-state change occurred.

tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerConRetry.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerConRetry
tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerConRetry.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerConRetry indicates number of peer connection retry attempts.

tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerStateTimer.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerStateTimer
tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerStateTimer.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerStateTimer indicates the number of seconds to wait before another message is sent to a peer.

tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerTimeout.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerTimeout
tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerTimeout.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerTimeout indicates the number of seconds to wait for a response from the peer before declaring the peer unavailable.

tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerSAAccepted.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerSAAccepted
tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerSAAccepted.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerSAAccepted indicates the number of entries in the source-active cache accepted from the peer.

tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerSARecvd.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerSARecvd
tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerSARecvd.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerSARecvd indicates the number of entries in the source-active cache received by the peer.

tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerLastASLimit.name: tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerLastASLimit
tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerLastASLimit.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerGrpPeerLastASLimit indicates the time that the last active source limit was triggered.

tmnxMsdpSourceTable.name: tmnxMsdpSourceTable
tmnxMsdpSourceTable.description: The tmnxMsdpSourceTable provides a listing of all MSDP Source configuration.

tmnxMsdpSourceEntry.name: tmnxMsdpSourceEntry
tmnxMsdpSourceEntry.description: An tmnxMsdpSourceEntry represents a MSDP Source configuration. Entries can be created and deleted via SNMP SET operations.

tmnxMsdpSourcePrefixType.name: tmnxMsdpSourcePrefixType
tmnxMsdpSourcePrefixType.description: The value of tmnxMsdpSourcePrefixType indicates the type of tmnxMsdpSourcePrefix.

tmnxMsdpSourcePrefix.name: tmnxMsdpSourcePrefix
tmnxMsdpSourcePrefix.description: The value of tmnxMsdpSourcePrefix indicates the IP address of the sources from which the source active messages would be accepted.

tmnxMsdpSourceMask.name: tmnxMsdpSourceMask
tmnxMsdpSourceMask.description: The value of tmnxMsdpSourceMask indicates the mask to be used along with tmnxMsdpSourcePrefix to obtain the range of addresses from which the router can accept source active messages.

tmnxMsdpSourceRowStatus.name: tmnxMsdpSourceRowStatus
tmnxMsdpSourceRowStatus.description: tmnxMsdpSourceRowStatus is the object used for creating and deleting row entries in this table.

tmnxMsdpSourceMaxActiveSources.name: tmnxMsdpSourceMaxActiveSources
tmnxMsdpSourceMaxActiveSources.description: The value of tmnxMsdpSourceMaxActiveSources specifies the maximum number of source active messages that will be accepted by MSDP. This effectively controls the number of active sources that can be stored on the system. By default, no limit is placed on the number of source active messages and this is specified by the value '-1'. A value of 0 means that no source active messages will be accepted.

tmnxMsdpSourceDiscMethod.name: tmnxMsdpSourceDiscMethod
tmnxMsdpSourceDiscMethod.description: The value of tmnxMsdpSourceDiscMethod indicates the discovery method for this multicast source. If the source entry was created by an user, the value of this field is 'configured'. If the source was created dynamically, the value is 'dynamic'

tmnxMsdpSourceSrcActMsgsExMax.name: tmnxMsdpSourceSrcActMsgsExMax
tmnxMsdpSourceSrcActMsgsExMax.description: The value of tmnxMsdpSourceSrcActMsgsExMax indicates the number of source active messages received from this source that exceeded the established maximum number.

tmnxMsdpSourceLastExEventTime.name: tmnxMsdpSourceLastExEventTime
tmnxMsdpSourceLastExEventTime.description: The value of tmnxMsdpSourceLastExEventTime indicates the time the last exceed event was triggered.

tmnxMsdpSrcActiveTable.name: tmnxMsdpSrcActiveTable
tmnxMsdpSrcActiveTable.description: The tmnxMsdpSrcActiveTable table stores the MSDP Source Active(SA) advertisements currently in the MSDP speaker's cache.

tmnxMsdpSrcActiveEntry.name: tmnxMsdpSrcActiveEntry
tmnxMsdpSrcActiveEntry.description: An entry representing an MSDP SA advertisement. The INDEX to this table includes msdpSACacheOriginRP for diagnosing incorrect MSDP advertisements; normally a Source and Group pair would be unique. This is a read-only table.

tmnxMsdpSrcActiveGroupAddrType.name: tmnxMsdpSrcActiveGroupAddrType
tmnxMsdpSrcActiveGroupAddrType.description: The value of tmnxMsdpSrcActiveGroupAddrType indicates the address type of tmnxMsdpSrcActiveGroupAddr.

tmnxMsdpSrcActiveGroupAddr.name: tmnxMsdpSrcActiveGroupAddr
tmnxMsdpSrcActiveGroupAddr.description: The value of tmnxMsdpSrcActiveGroupAddr indicates the group address of the Source Active entry.

tmnxMsdpSrcActiveSourceAddrType.name: tmnxMsdpSrcActiveSourceAddrType
tmnxMsdpSrcActiveSourceAddrType.description: The value of tmnxMsdpSrcActiveSourceAddrType indicates the address type of tmnxMsdpSrcActiveSourceAddr.

tmnxMsdpSrcActiveSourceAddr.name: tmnxMsdpSrcActiveSourceAddr
tmnxMsdpSrcActiveSourceAddr.description: The value of tmnxMsdpSrcActiveSourceAddr indicates the source address of the Source Active entry.

tmnxMsdpSrcActiveOriginRPType.name: tmnxMsdpSrcActiveOriginRPType
tmnxMsdpSrcActiveOriginRPType.description: The value of tmnxMsdpSrcActiveOriginRPType indicates the address type of tmnxMsdpSrcActiveOriginRP.

tmnxMsdpSrcActiveOriginRP.name: tmnxMsdpSrcActiveOriginRP
tmnxMsdpSrcActiveOriginRP.description: The value of tmnxMsdpSrcActiveOriginRP indicates the origin RP address of the Source Active entry.

tmnxMsdpSrcActivePrLearnFrType.name: tmnxMsdpSrcActivePrLearnFrType
tmnxMsdpSrcActivePrLearnFrType.description: The value of tmnxMsdpSrcActivePrLearnFrType indicates the address type of tmnxMsdpSrcActivePeerLearntFrom.

tmnxMsdpSrcActivePeerLearntFrom.name: tmnxMsdpSrcActivePeerLearntFrom
tmnxMsdpSrcActivePeerLearntFrom.description: The value of tmnxMsdpSrcActivePeerLearntFrom indicates the peer from which this Source Active entry was last accepted.

tmnxMsdpSrcActiveRPFPeerType.name: tmnxMsdpSrcActiveRPFPeerType
tmnxMsdpSrcActiveRPFPeerType.description: The value of tmnxMsdpSrcActiveRPFPeerType indicates the address type of tmnxMsdpSrcActiveRPFPeer.

tmnxMsdpSrcActiveRPFPeer.name: tmnxMsdpSrcActiveRPFPeer
tmnxMsdpSrcActiveRPFPeer.description: The value of tmnxMsdpSrcActiveRPFPeer indicates the peer from which an SA message corresponding to this cache entry would be accepted (i.e. the RPF peer for tmnxMsdpSrcActiveOriginRP). This may be different than tmnxMsdpSrcActivePeerLearntFrom if this entry was created by an MSDP SA-Response.

tmnxMsdpSrcActiveUpTime.name: tmnxMsdpSrcActiveUpTime
tmnxMsdpSrcActiveUpTime.description: The value of tmnxMsdpSrcActiveUpTime indicates the time since this entry was first placed in the Source Active (SA) cache. It is the difference between the time that the entry was first placed in the SA cache and the current time.

tmnxMsdpSrcActiveExpiryTime.name: tmnxMsdpSrcActiveExpiryTime
tmnxMsdpSrcActiveExpiryTime.description: The value of tmnxMsdpSrcActiveExpiryTime indicates the time remaining before this entry will expire from the Source Active (SA) cache. It is difference between the current time and the time that the entry will expire.

tmnxMsdpPeerStatsTable.name: tmnxMsdpPeerStatsTable
tmnxMsdpPeerStatsTable.description: The table tmnxMsdpPeerStatsTable is the statistics information related to a MSDP peer.

tmnxMsdpPeerStatsEntry.name: tmnxMsdpPeerStatsEntry
tmnxMsdpPeerStatsEntry.description: tmnxMsdpPeerStatsEntry is an entry (conceptual row) in the tmnxMsdpPeerStatsTable. Each entry represents a MSDP peer related statistics information.

tmnxMsdpPeerStatsActSrcLimExcd.name: tmnxMsdpPeerStatsActSrcLimExcd
tmnxMsdpPeerStatsActSrcLimExcd.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerStatsActSrcLimExcd indicates the number of times the global active source limit has been exceeded by this peer instance.

tmnxMsdpPeerStatsLastStChange.name: tmnxMsdpPeerStatsLastStChange
tmnxMsdpPeerStatsLastStChange.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerStatsLastStChange indicates how long ago the peer state changed.

tmnxMsdpPeerStatsLastMsgPeer.name: tmnxMsdpPeerStatsLastMsgPeer
tmnxMsdpPeerStatsLastMsgPeer.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerStatsLastMsgPeer indicates how long ago the last message was received from this peer instance.

tmnxMsdpPeerStatsRPFFailures.name: tmnxMsdpPeerStatsRPFFailures
tmnxMsdpPeerStatsRPFFailures.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerStatsRPFFailures indicates number of reverse path forwarding (RPF) failures.

tmnxMsdpPeerStatsRemoteCloses.name: tmnxMsdpPeerStatsRemoteCloses
tmnxMsdpPeerStatsRemoteCloses.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerStatsRemoteCloses indicates the number of times the remote peer closed.

tmnxMsdpPeerStatsPeerTimeouts.name: tmnxMsdpPeerStatsPeerTimeouts
tmnxMsdpPeerStatsPeerTimeouts.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerStatsPeerTimeouts indicates the number of peer timeouts.

tmnxMsdpPeerStatsSAMsgsSent.name: tmnxMsdpPeerStatsSAMsgsSent
tmnxMsdpPeerStatsSAMsgsSent.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerStatsSAMsgsSent indicates the number of source-active messages sent.

tmnxMsdpPeerStatsSAMsgsRecvd.name: tmnxMsdpPeerStatsSAMsgsRecvd
tmnxMsdpPeerStatsSAMsgsRecvd.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerStatsSAMsgsRecvd indicates the number of source-active messages received.

tmnxMsdpPeerStatsSAReqMsgsSent.name: tmnxMsdpPeerStatsSAReqMsgsSent
tmnxMsdpPeerStatsSAReqMsgsSent.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerStatsSAReqMsgsSent indicates the number of source-active request messages sent.

tmnxMsdpPeerStatsSAReqMsgsRecvd.name: tmnxMsdpPeerStatsSAReqMsgsRecvd
tmnxMsdpPeerStatsSAReqMsgsRecvd.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerStatsSAReqMsgsRecvd indicates the number of source-active request messages received.

tmnxMsdpPeerStatsSAResMsgsSent.name: tmnxMsdpPeerStatsSAResMsgsSent
tmnxMsdpPeerStatsSAResMsgsSent.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerStatsSAResMsgsSent indicates the number of source-active response messages sent.

tmnxMsdpPeerStatsSAResMsgsRecvd.name: tmnxMsdpPeerStatsSAResMsgsRecvd
tmnxMsdpPeerStatsSAResMsgsRecvd.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerStatsSAResMsgsRecvd indicates the number of source-active response messages received.

tmnxMsdpPeerStatsKAMsgsSent.name: tmnxMsdpPeerStatsKAMsgsSent
tmnxMsdpPeerStatsKAMsgsSent.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerStatsKAMsgsSent indicates the number of keep-alive messages sent.

tmnxMsdpPeerStatsKAMsgsRecvd.name: tmnxMsdpPeerStatsKAMsgsRecvd
tmnxMsdpPeerStatsKAMsgsRecvd.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerStatsKAMsgsRecvd indicates the number of keep-alive messages received.

tmnxMsdpPeerStatsUnknMsgsRecvd.name: tmnxMsdpPeerStatsUnknMsgsRecvd
tmnxMsdpPeerStatsUnknMsgsRecvd.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerStatsUnknMsgsRecvd indicates the number of unknown messages received.

tmnxMsdpPeerStatsErrorMsgsRecvd.name: tmnxMsdpPeerStatsErrorMsgsRecvd
tmnxMsdpPeerStatsErrorMsgsRecvd.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerStatsErrorMsgsRecvd indicates number of error messages received.

tmnxMsdpPeerStatsSALearnt.name: tmnxMsdpPeerStatsSALearnt
tmnxMsdpPeerStatsSALearnt.description: The value of tmnxMsdpPeerStatsSALearnt indicates the number of unique source active entries in the cache learned from the peer.
